---
import SiteLayout from '../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

export const meta = {
  title: 'LaGuardia Runway Disaster: Air Canada Flight Severed in Fatal Collision With Fire Truck',
  description: 'Two pilots are dead and 41 injured after Air Canada Flight AC8646 violently collided with a responding fire truck on a LaGuardia Airport runway. Federal authorities have launched a major investigation as witnesses describe the chaotic scene.',
  category: 'us',
  published: '2026-03-24',
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "NewsArticle",
  "headline": meta.title,
  "description": meta.description,
  "datePublished": meta.published,
  "dateModified": meta.published,
  "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Trunk Press" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Trunk Press" },
  "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://trunkpress.photonbuilder.com/like-the-plane-got-cut-in-half-laguardia" }
};
---

<SiteLayout site="trunkpress" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://trunkpress.photonbuilder.com/like-the-plane-got-cut-in-half-laguardia" schema={schema}>
  <article class="tp-article max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-12">
    <!-- Category + Date -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-[2px] uppercase text-[var(--accent-color)]">🇺🇸 US</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-[var(--text-secondary)]">March 24, 2026</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-4 text-[var(--text-primary)]">
      LaGuardia Runway Disaster: Air Canada Flight Severed in Fatal Collision With Fire Truck
    </h1>

    <!-- Lede -->
    <p class="font-bold text-lg text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--accent-color)] pl-4">
      An Air Canada passenger jet arriving from Montreal collided violently with a fire truck on a LaGuardia Airport runway late Sunday night, killing both pilots and injuring 41 others. Authorities are investigating the chaotic sequence of events that left witnesses describing the aircraft as looking "like the plane got cut in half."
    </p>

    <!-- Article body -->
    <div class="space-y-5 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">What Happened</h2>
      <p>
        At 23:40 local time on Sunday, Air Canada flight AC8646 touched down at New York's LaGuardia Airport and immediately encountered disaster. The aircraft struck a firefighting vehicle that was reportedly responding to a separate incident on the tarmac involving another plane reporting an odor issue. The sheer force of the collision resulted in immediate catastrophic damage to the arriving jet.
      </p>
      <p>
        Both pilots operating the aircraft, including 30-year-old Québec native Antoine Forest, were killed in the crash. The Federal Aviation Administration described the loss of the two young aviators as an "absolute tragedy." Additionally, 41 individuals—including two occupants of the fire engine—were transported to local hospitals. While many have since been released, several remain treated for serious injuries.
      </p>
      <p>
        Witnesses described a terrifying ordeal. Passengers reported heavy turbulence during descent, followed by a rough landing and the violent jolt of the pilot attempting emergency braking. "As you heard the brake, a couple seconds later it was just a very loud boom," said passenger Rebecca Liquori. Another witness on a nearby plane, 23-year-old Leo Medina, stated, "It was like the plane got cut in half."
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">The Investigation Commences</h2>
      <p>
        The National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) has launched a full-scale investigation into the fatal collision. NTSB Chairwoman Jennifer Homendy confirmed that her team arrived on-site shortly after 03:00 local time on Monday to begin documenting the extensive debris field and analyzing crucial evidence.
      </p>
      <p>
        Crucially, investigators have recovered the aircraft's cockpit voice recorder and flight data recorder, which survived the crash undamaged. Preliminary audio from the LaGuardia air traffic control tower reveals a desperate, last-second warning from a staff member yelling, "'Truck One, stop, stop, stop!" just moments before impact.
      </p>
      <p>
        The runway remains closed as federal investigators meticulously process the scene. This marks the first deadly incident at LaGuardia in over 34 years, shattering the airport's long-standing safety record and prompting urgent questions about ground communication protocols and tarmac safety measures.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">Compounding Crises in Air Travel</h2>
      <p>
        The LaGuardia crash occurs against a backdrop of severe operational strain within the U.S. aviation system. The ongoing shutdown of the Department of Homeland Security has left Transportation Security Administration (TSA) agents working without pay for over a month. This has triggered significant staffing shortages, massive security lines, and widespread disruptions across major hubs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Even the NTSB's rapid response was hindered by these systemic failures. Chairwoman Homendy revealed that an essential air traffic control specialist assigned to the investigation was stuck in a TSA security line in Houston for three hours, delaying the team's complete deployment to New York.
      </p>
      <p>
        The convergence of a fatal runway incursion and crippling security infrastructure delays paints a grim picture of the current state of American air travel, amplifying safety concerns among passengers and aviation professionals alike.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">Why It Matters</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond the immediate tragedy, the incident highlights critical vulnerabilities in airport ground operations. The collision between an arriving commercial flight and an active emergency vehicle underscores potential catastrophic failures in situational awareness and air traffic coordination that demand immediate regulatory scrutiny.
      </p>
      <p>
        Furthermore, the crash starkly demonstrates the life-saving necessity of basic safety protocols. Following his visit to the crash site, U.S. Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy emphasized that the survival of many passengers was directly attributable to adherence to safety measures. "As you see from last night, they do save lives," Duffy stated regarding the use of seat belts.
      </p>
      <p>
        As investigations proceed, the aviation industry faces intense pressure to rectify the systemic communication breakdowns that led to this disaster, ensuring that emergency responses do not themselves become the cause of fatal collisions on active runways.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Tags -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--border-color)]">
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#LaGuardia</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#AirCanada</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#AviationSafety</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#NTSB</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#NewYork</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Related -->
    <div class="mt-8 p-5 bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-black tracking-wider text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2">RELATED STORIES</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">More coverage coming. This is a developing story.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
